\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 Heat a deep large skillet with 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil over medium-high heat. Add bacon and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/crisp/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 crisp}} 3 to 4 minutes. Add onions, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 garlic}}, bay leaf and mushrooms, season with salt and pepper and cook until tender but not browned, 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/crush/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 crush}} them up with a wooden spoon and simmer 15 minutes on low heat.\
Season the fish with salt and pepper. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dust/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Dust}} fish with flour and shake off excess.\
Heat 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil in a large skillet over medium high heat. Cook {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/fish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 fish}} 4 minutes on each side.\
While fish cooks, return sauce to bubble and stir in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mascarpone/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 mascarpone}} cheese. Adjust seasoning.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa180\ql\qnatural
\cf2 Remove fish from skillet to a platter and cover loosely with foil to keep warm. Reduce heat to medium and add butter to pan. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/brown-butter/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Brown butter}}, 2 to 3 minutes, stir in balsamic and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 simmer}} 1 to 2 minutes to reduce by half. Pour the brown butter and vinegar over fish.\
